<div class="textHome">

 <p>
  Welcome to the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Professional Awards website!  Each year USACE recognizes 
  employees' contributions of excellence in performance, leadership, professional development and 
  community support in the fields of architecture, landscape architecture, interior design, 
  computer aided design &amp; building information modeling, structural engineering, fire protection engineering, mechanical engineering, electrical engineering, and the geospatial and control systems.
 </p>

  The 2021 awards will include:  
  <div class="homeBlock" style="margin-top:5px;">
    Architect of the Year<br>
    Landscape Architect of the Year<br>
    Interior Designer of the Year<br>
    CAD/BIM Professional of the Year<br>
    Structural Engineer of the Year<br>
    Fire Protection Engineer of the Year<br>
    Mechanical Engineer of the Year<br>
    Electrical Engineer of the Year<br>
    Geospatial Professional of the Year<br>
    Control System Professional of the Year <span style="color:#cc0000; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold;">* NEW *</span>
  </div>
 
 <p>
  Anyone may access the instructions and information on the previous awardees but only USACE 
  activities may submit nominations. Do this by registering, and then logging on to the nomination 
  section of the site.  After the nomination period concludes, a jury consisting of the leaders from 
  the appropriate Communities of Practice and additional qualified USACE peers will judge the 
  nominations based on the five evaluation factors outlined in the "Instructions" page and recommend 
  selections to the Chief of the Engineering and Construction for confirmation.
 </p>
